<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,775,1077,1677]" box="[132,232,1077,1103]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,775,1077,1677]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Bornmüller first supposed this species to be a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosissimus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">E. villosissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but later described it as species. 
<bibRefCitation author="BORNMULLER J. F. N." box="[569,775,1140,1167]" firstAuthor="Bornmuller" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="200 - 228" part="36" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/60075927" refId="ref2229" refString="BORNMULLER J. F. N. 1918. - Revisions-Ergebnisse einiger orientalischer und zentralasiatischer Arten der Gattung Echinops. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 36 (2): 200 - 228. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 60075927" title="Revisions-Ergebnisse einiger orientalischer und zentralasiatischer Arten der Gattung Echinops" type="journal article" year="1918">Bornmüller (1918)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[235,435,1172,1198]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lalesarensis">
<emphasis box="[235,435,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Echinops lalesarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on collections of him from Lalesar, but did not designate a holotype nor did mention the name of the herbarium where the specimens were housed. Subsequently, fifteen specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[502,641,1268,1294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lalesarensis">
<emphasis box="[502,641,1268,1294]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">E. lalesarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected by Bornmüller from Lalesar were found at different herbaria. Of these, the specimen B100093507 is better preserved and more complete than the other specimens and best represents the species description given in the protologue, hence it is designated here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[130,775,1077,1677]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName box="[155,525,1459,1486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lalesarensis" variety="adenocaulis">
<emphasis box="[155,361,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Echinops lalesarensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[407,525,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">adenocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="BORNMULLER J. F. N." firstAuthor="Bornmuller" journalOrPublisher="Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="200 - 228" part="36" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/60075927" refId="ref2229" refString="BORNMULLER J. F. N. 1918. - Revisions-Ergebnisse einiger orientalischer und zentralasiatischer Arten der Gattung Echinops. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 36 (2): 200 - 228. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 60075927" title="Revisions-Ergebnisse einiger orientalischer und zentralasiatischer Arten der Gattung Echinops" type="journal article" year="1918">Bornmüller (1918)</bibRefCitation>
. According to him, it is distinguished from the typical variety by having glandular indumentum on stem. In their account, 
<bibRefCitation author="MONTAZEROLGHAEM S. &amp; RAHIMINEJAD M. R. &amp; MOZAFFARIAN V. &amp; SUSANNA A." box="[295,635,1555,1582]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Montazerolghaem" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="81 - 97" part="263" refId="ref2423" refString="MONTAZEROLGHAEM S., RAHIMINEJAD M. R., MOZAFFARIAN V. &amp; SUSANNA A. 2016. - Taxonomic notes on the genus Echinops (Compositae, Cardueae-Echinopsinae) from Iran. Phytotaxa 263 (2): 81 - 97. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 263.2.1" title="Taxonomic notes on the genus Echinops (Compositae, Cardueae-Echinopsinae) from Iran" type="journal article" year="2016">
Montazerolghaem 
<emphasis box="[498,551,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, considering morphological data, placed 
<taxonomicName box="[435,598,1587,1614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="lalesarensis" variety="adenocaulis">
var. 
<emphasis box="[479,598,1587,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">adenocaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[133,271,1619,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Echinops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lalesarensis">
<emphasis box="[133,271,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">E. lalesarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Montazerolghaem 
<emphasis box="[482,531,1619,1645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
’s treatment is followed here. Anyway a lectotype for this taxon is chosen here too.
</paragraph>
